</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1269,2016]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Note: Considering that species in the group ascutellaris have very similar habitus and aedeagus, and considering that more than one species can be found in the same locality, we understand that this record should be considered with caution.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1269,2016]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,430,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Short Redescription.</emphasis>
Eyes normal (
<figureCitation box="[591,674,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Winged. Last antennomere wide, with a short conic projection medially (
<figureCitation box="[229,312,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). No posterior projections on male ventrites.Apex of the right lobe of the aedeagus as an upside-down trapezoid with the apical margin curved outward, with a pronounced curve to its left end (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1303,1700,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs. 44, 45</figureCitation>
). Flagellum shorter (about half the length) than aedeagus, with apex bent at 90º (
<figureCitation box="[933,1073,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs. 41, 42</figureCitation>
). Proportion aedeagus/elytron = 0.28. Anterior sides of spiculum gastrale of the genital segment widening towards the apex, resulting in a pawnshaped spiculum gastrale, with the apical width about twice as wide as the rounded base (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1243,1809,1836]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Male mesotibia regularly curved internally (
<figureCitation box="[468,552,1844,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca with 2-turns placed close to the spermatheca base, followed by a short and curved body ending in a sharp curve before the rounded apical bulb (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1141,1880,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). Proportion spermatheca/ elytron = 0.12.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1269,2016]" box="[199,1115,1953,1980]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,344,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[350,450,1953,1979]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
: known only from 
<typeStatus box="[661,709,1954,1980]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality (original description; here).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1269,2016]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,433,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Taxonomic Remarks.</emphasis>
As proposed in Gnaspini (1996: 539) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Peck, S. B. &amp; P. Gnaspini &amp; A. F. Newton" box="[902,1143,1989,2016]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="37 - 72" refId="ref44075" refString="Peck, S. B., P. Gnaspini, and A. F. Newton. (1998) Catalogue and generic keys for the Leiodidae of Mexico State, West Indies, and Central and South America (Insecta: Coleoptera). Giornale Italiano de Entomologia, 9, 37 - 72." type="journal article" year="1998">
Peck 
<emphasis box="[963,1011,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (1998: 62)
</bibRefCitation>
, all subspecies of 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. brun- nea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[199,347,153,179]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 433" refId="ref43714" refString="Jeannel, R. (1936) Monographie des Catopidae. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, New Series, 1, 1 - 433." type="journal article" year="1936">Jeannel 1936</bibRefCitation>
are here raised to species status. The combination of the variation observed on aedeagus, genital segment, eyes, antenna, male mesotibia, and spermatheca allow taxon recognition (see discussion under each of these taxa).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Szymczakowski, 1975" authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" box="[395,807,260,287]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis" status="n. stat.">
<emphasis box="[395,544,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. brevicollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Szymczakowski, W." box="[553,807,260,287]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="13 - 24" refId="ref45031" refString="Szymczakowski, W. (1975) Formes cavernicoles d' Adelopsis brunneus Jeann. du Venezuela et de l'Ile de Trinidad (Coleoptera: Catopidae). Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Espeleologia, 6, 13 - 24." type="journal article" year="1975">Szymczakowski, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[816,892,261,287]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">n. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[908,1047,260,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 41–45</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Szymczakowski, 1975" authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" box="[1068,1436,260,287]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azzalii" status="n. stat.">
<emphasis box="[1068,1174,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. azzalii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Szymczakowski, W." box="[1183,1436,260,287]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="13 - 24" refId="ref45031" refString="Szymczakowski, W. (1975) Formes cavernicoles d' Adelopsis brunneus Jeann. du Venezuela et de l'Ile de Trinidad (Coleoptera: Catopidae). Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Espeleologia, 6, 13 - 24." type="journal article" year="1975">Szymczakowski, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,225,297,323]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">n. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[240,376,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–40" captionStartId="15.[151,264,911,936]" captionTargetBox="[181,1401,175,886]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[181,1407,174,892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–40. Adelopsis azzalii Szymczakowski, 1975 new status. 28–30, (probable) holotype male in CBCV, from Cueva de Hueque. 28, genital segment; 29, antenna, dorsal view; 30, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 31–39, additional male (same data). 31–35, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 36, head, lateral view; 37, protarsus and protibia; 38, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 39, metatarsus and metatibia; 40, female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 28, 31–35, 40; b for figs. 29, 30, 36–39." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542775/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 31–35</figureCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeannel, 1936" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1936" box="[443,702,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis box="[443,541,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. ovalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[548,702,297,323]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 433" refId="ref43714" refString="Jeannel, R. (1936) Monographie des Catopidae. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, New Series, 1, 1 - 433." type="journal article" year="1936">Jeannel, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[717,852,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,1340,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,1334,1866]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 17–25. Adelopsis ovalis Jeannel, 1936, holotype male in MNHN, from ‘Venezuela’. 17–20, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, and right lateral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 21, head, lateral view; 22, antenna, dorsal view; 23, protarsus and protibia; 24, mesotibia; 25, metatibia. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 17–20; b for figs. 21–25." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542771/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 17–20</figureCitation>
) are very similar to each other. The first two species have male mesotibia curved (
<figureCitation box="[481,574,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–40" captionStartId="15.[151,264,911,936]" captionTargetBox="[181,1401,175,886]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[181,1407,174,892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–40. Adelopsis azzalii Szymczakowski, 1975 new status. 28–30, (probable) holotype male in CBCV, from Cueva de Hueque. 28, genital segment; 29, antenna, dorsal view; 30, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 31–39, additional male (same data). 31–35, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 36, head, lateral view; 37, protarsus and protibia; 38, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 39, metatarsus and metatibia; 40, female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 28, 31–35, 40; b for figs. 29, 30, 36–39." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542775/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[586,615,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">51</figureCitation>
) whereas the latter species has it bent medially (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1243,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,1340,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,1334,1866]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 17–25. Adelopsis ovalis Jeannel, 1936, holotype male in MNHN, from ‘Venezuela’. 17–20, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, and right lateral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 21, head, lateral view; 22, antenna, dorsal view; 23, protarsus and protibia; 24, mesotibia; 25, metatibia. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 17–20; b for figs. 21–25." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542771/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), and this is used to separate the first two from the latter (see also Taxonomic Remarks under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[1007,1169,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ascutellaris">
<emphasis box="[1007,1169,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. ascutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, above). The eyes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Szymczakowski" baseAuthorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seem to be larger than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Szymczakowski" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[616,719,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azzalii">
<emphasis box="[616,719,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. azzalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[733,826,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 47</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[836,865,405,432]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–40" captionStartId="15.[151,264,911,936]" captionTargetBox="[181,1401,175,886]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[181,1407,174,892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–40. Adelopsis azzalii Szymczakowski, 1975 new status. 28–30, (probable) holotype male in CBCV, from Cueva de Hueque. 28, genital segment; 29, antenna, dorsal view; 30, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 31–39, additional male (same data). 31–35, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 36, head, lateral view; 37, protarsus and protibia; 38, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 39, metatarsus and metatibia; 40, female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 28, 31–35, 40; b for figs. 29, 30, 36–39." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542775/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">36</figureCitation>
) and the spermathecae seem different too (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1431,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1054,1079]" captionTargetBox="[158,1401,334,1030]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1408,327,1035]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41–53. Adelopsis brevicollis Szymczakowski, 1975, new status. 41-52, topotype male in SBPC, from Oilbird Cave. 41–45, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 46, genital segment; 47, head, lateral view; 48, antenna, dorsal view; 49, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 50, protarsus and protibia; 51, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 52, metatarsus and metatibia; 53, topotype female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 41–46, 53; b for figs. 47–52." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542777/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,183,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–40" captionStartId="15.[151,264,911,936]" captionTargetBox="[181,1401,175,886]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[181,1407,174,892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 28–40. Adelopsis azzalii Szymczakowski, 1975 new status. 28–30, (probable) holotype male in CBCV, from Cueva de Hueque. 28, genital segment; 29, antenna, dorsal view; 30, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 31–39, additional male (same data). 31–35, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views, and frontal view of aedeagus apex; 36, head, lateral view; 37, protarsus and protibia; 38, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 39, metatarsus and metatibia; 40, female (same data), spermatheca. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 28, 31–35, 40; b for figs. 29, 30, 36–39." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542775/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">40</figureCitation>
). Yet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Szymczakowski" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[252,400,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis box="[252,400,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from a cave in 
<collectingCountry box="[702,800,441,467]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szymczakowski" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Szymczakowski" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[909,1012,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Adelopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azzalii">
<emphasis box="[909,1012,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. azzalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from a cave in 
<collectingCountry box="[1314,1433,441,467]" name="Venezuela" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. Therefore, we here prefer to keep the species cited above as a separate species, but we intend to make a more careful examination, including the analysis of the 
<typeStatus box="[626,685,513,539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">types</typeStatus>
of all species in the group.
</paragraph>
